Import the Turtle and random modules.

Create the screen, paddles, and ball with their initial properties.

Define functions to move the ball and paddles.

Keep track of the score and update it when the ball hits the opponent's side.

Determine the game outcome by checking if either player has reached the maximum score.

Use a while loop to continuously update the ball and paddle movements, check for collisions and score updates, and check for the game outcome.

Delete the Turtle objects and close the screen when the game is over.